title: College Roundup: Bryant's two late goals lifts Elmira
text:
College Roundup: Bryant's two late goals lifts Elmira Ron Levanduski, rlevanduski@stargazette.com | @SGRLevanduski 8:46 p.m. EDT October 14, 2015 Michael Bryant scored two goals five minutes apart late in the second half to lead Elmira to a 3-2 win over SUNY Canton in a non-conference game at Elmira. Elmira's Michael Bryant controls the ball in Wednesday's game with SUNY Canton. (Photo: Provided by Elmira College) CONNECT 4 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Michael Bryant scored two late goals to rally the Elmira College men's soccer team to a 3-2 victory over SUNY Canton in a non-conference game Wednesday afternoon at Campus Field in Elmira. 
The Kangeroos led 2-0 at the half on a pair of goals by Edward Malinoski Jr. Tony Barraco closed the deficit to 2-1 just 11 seconds into the second half before Bryant’s heroics. Malinoski, who leads the Empire 8 Conference in scoring, connected on goals five minutes apart with the game-winner coming at the 79 minute, 45 second mark on a header off of a corner kick from Barraco. 
The Soaring Eagles held an 8-3 advantage in shots on goal and a 9-3 edge in corner kicks. Elmira improved to 5-4-3 and extended its unbeaten streak to seven games. 
Niagara County Community College 5, Corning 3: At Corning, 2015 Elmira Notre Dame graduate Li Malingou scored a hat trick for the Red Barons (4-9) in a National Junior College Athletic Association Region III loss to the Thunderwolves. 
Women’s Soccer 
Corning Community College 6, Niagara County Community College 1: At Corning, Alyssa Crawford scored two goals to lead the Red Barons (3-10) to a NJCAA Region III win over the Thunderwolves. Read or Share this story: http://stargaz.tt/1RIQLxI TOP VIDEOS
